The surgeon general of the SANDF says three of the cases are from the Western Cape and one is in Gauteng. CAPE TOWN - Four positive cases of COVID-19 have been confirmed within the South African National Defence Force community. The surgeon general of the SANDF, Lieutenant-General Zola Dabula, says three of the cases are from the Western Cape and one is in Gauteng. READ: Not all soldiers use excessive force: DMV chair According to a statement, none of the cases involves uniformed members or members who've been deployed to support the police. The defence force said it's also identified quarantine and isolation facilities for the military community. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.